@gzsombor: We would like to know your opinion on this as well.
I personally think it would be best to return "" here, but @TobiGr thinks we should return a link to YouTube's logo, as we always return a URL for all other kind of playlists, however @TheAssassin thinks we should avoid logos/brands.
Either way, in the NewPipe front-end, we're gonna check if service ID equals YouTube's service ID and call YoutubeParsingHelper's function to check whether the playlist ID is a mix. When that's the case, NewPipe will replace it with a radio icon embedded in our app.

@gzsombor As a user of the extractor, what solution do you prefer?
The YouTube logo, an empty string or a constant?
@mauriciocolli @wb9688 I'd be okay with returning nothing, too

What about returning a AvatarIcon class, something like this:
class AvatarIcon {
   String url;
   IconType type;
   enum IconType { YOUTUBE_LOGO, OTHER_LOGO, .... }
}


Either the url or the type would be filled - if the URL the frontend could use that, if not, it should revert to some custom magic.

@gzsombor That's basically done in #268. So we should wait for this PR to be merged. Let's go with the empty string for now and change this later in or after #268
